 Dutywa - Dutywa police arrested a 29-year-old man for possession of unlicensed firearm and one round of ammunition. "The suspect was arrested on Sunday, at about 00:05, at Drayini Locality, Ngcingwane Village, Dutywa," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The suspect will appear before the Dutywa Magistrate’s Court on Monday on charges of possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 